  "prompt": "Which tickets were sold by BookMyShow for Global Citizen Festival?",
  "response": "BookMyShow, a popular online ticketing platform, has sold tickets for various events, including the **Global Citizen Festival**, which is a music festival aimed at raising awareness and funds to combat extreme poverty. The festival typically features performances by renowned artists and speakers advocating for global issues.\n\nWhile specific ticket details can vary by year and location, BookMyShow generally offers tickets in the following categories for the **Global Citizen Festival**:\n\n1. **General Admission (Free Tickets)**:  \n   - These are free tickets distributed through a lottery or reward system, requiring attendees to take specific actions (e.g., activism tasks) to earn them.  \n   - They provide access to the general standing area of the festival.\n\n2. **VIP or Premium Tickets**:  \n   - Paid tickets that offer enhanced experiences such as closer access to the stage, dedicated viewing areas, and access to VIP lounges.  \n   - These are usually limited in number and sold on a first-come, first-served basis.\n\n3. **Early Entry or Priority Tickets**:  \n   - Paid tickets that allow early access to the venue, ensuring better spots in the general admission area.\n\n4. **Group or Family Packages**:  \n   - Bundled tickets for groups or families, often at a discounted rate.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it\u2019s best to check **BookMyShow\u2019s official website or app** for ticket availability, pricing, and terms. The Global Citizen Festival organizers also provide details on their official platform regarding ticketing and entry requirements.",
